==English==

===Noun===
'''sewage''' (''[[uncountable]]'')
# A [[suspension]] of liquid and solid [[waste]], and water [[runoff]], transported by [[sewer]]s to be [[dispose]]d of or [[process]]ed.
# ''(Obsolete usage)'' [[w:sewerage|sewerage]].

===Etymology===
Via Old [[French]] ''essouier'' = "to [[drain]]" from Late [[Latin]] ''exaquare''. The formal Latin antecedents of "[[sewer]]" and "sewage" are ''exaquarium'' and ''exaquaticum''.

